</i></p><p class="sc-dtMgUX eyUPwo pf-14_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3"><span style="color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">In healthcare, the question of whether children can consent to medical treatment is both complex and crucial. It touches upon fundamental issues of autonomy, protection, and the delicate balance between parental authority and a child's rights. In this blog, Dr Richard Dune delves into understanding the legal framework and ethical considerations surrounding this topic, which is essential for healthcare professionals, parents, and young individuals alike.</span>
